"{\"uid\": \"english.aawsat.com-varieties-5037785-pariss-moulin-rouge-inaugurates-new-windmill-sails-ahead-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris's Moulin Rouge cabaret club, whose landmark windmill sails fell down in April, inaugurated its new blades on Friday, nearly a week before the Olympic torch was due to pass the venue.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.740619570575527e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 20, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8868500499522447e-45, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several hundred delighted locals and tourists gathered outside the club, one of the most visited attractions in the French capital, to celebrate the four red blades, decked out in gold and red, AFP reported.\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 306, \"end\": 312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7482279226409366, \"rank\": 0.23350751323233251, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 384, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.339833220918084e-14, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The windmill without its wings is a void for Paris, it was just sad,\\\" said managing director Jean-Victor Clerico, who runs the family business that attracts 600,000 visitors every year.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.740619570575527e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The idea was to be ready for the Olympic Games,\\\" he added, which begin on July 26.\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 670, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic torch is due to pass the venue on July 15.\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.698964464566783e-20, \"text\": \"Olympic torch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A show of French cancan, the wild traditional dance from Jacques Offenbach's operettas of the early 19th century, was performed in front of the club on Friday by dancers in traditional petticoats and frills.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 738, \"end\": 751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Cancan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French cancan\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Cancan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Cancan\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Offenbach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Offenbach\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Offenbach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Offenbach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I live in the neighbourhood and the Moulin Rouge has been part of my life for 65 years.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8868500499522447e-45, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a fan of dancing, the French cancan, bubbles and good humour,\\\" Nicole Doucin, 86, told AFP.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1053, \"end\": 1066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Cancan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French cancan\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Cancan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Cancan\"}, {\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.339833220918084e-14, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I heard of the inauguration on TikTok and I have always wanted to come to a show but it's so expensive, so it's so cool to watch this,\\\" said Autumn Mannsfeld, 25, from California.\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1156, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.701336498231052e-48, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.383746113418278e-16, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sails fell down on the night of April 25.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first three letters on the cabaret's facade -- M, O and U -- also fell off.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No one was injured in the incident.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The club's management has said it has ruled out any \\\"malicious act\\\".\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The birthplace of the cancan and the location for Baz Luhrmann's film \\\"Moulin Rouge\\\", the club has since remained open to the public.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baz_Luhrmann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Baz Luhrmann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baz_Luhrmann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baz_Luhrmann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French first lady Brigitte Macron caught up with an old friend - a giant panda born in France - at the tail end Friday of a visit to China with President Emmanuel Macron.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1675, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7482279226409366, \"rank\": 0.23350751323233251, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brigitte Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998051753399, \"rank\": 9.708419709935011e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999995268855155, \"rank\": 4.6625125858211624e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At a panda reserve in southwest China that Yuan Meng now calls home, the first lady marveled at how big he has grown.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southwest_China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"southwest China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southwest_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southwest_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yuan Meng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She helped choose his name - which means \\\"accomplishment of a dream\\\" - when he was born in a French zoo in 2017.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2058, \"end\": 2064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7482279226409366, \"rank\": 0.23350751323233251, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When they are born, they are like this,\\\" she said, holding up two fingers a short distance apart.\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the chunky male roamed in his enclosure, feasting on bamboo and ignoring bystanders who cried out his name, hoping to elicit a reaction.\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They have a very independent character,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They do only what they want.\\\"\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For decades, China has deployed what's often called \\\"panda diplomacy\\\" to smooth and promote relations with other countries, gifting the animals to friendly nations and lending pandas to zoos overseas on commercial terms.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999995268855155, \"rank\": 4.6625125858211624e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emmanuel Macron's state visit this week to China, his fourth as president, included meetings with Chinese leader Xi Jinping and other officials, discussing Russia's war in Ukraine, trade ties and other issues.\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2676, \"end\": 2681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999995268855155, \"rank\": 4.6625125858211624e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paramount_leader\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chinese leader\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paramount_leader\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paramount_leader\"}, {\"begin\": 2746, \"end\": 2756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xi Jinping\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\"}, {\"begin\": 2789, \"end\": 2795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999998593757581, \"rank\": 1.406234037865509e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999618994487, \"rank\": 3.808128655363295e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The China Wildlife Conservation Association said during the visit that it signed a letter of intent to send two of the animals to the Beauval Zoo south of Paris in 2027 under what would be a new 10-year round of panda cooperation with France.\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2848, \"end\": 2853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999995268855155, \"rank\": 4.6625125858211624e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2978, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ZooParc_de_Beauval\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beauval Zoo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ZooParc_de_Beauval\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ZooParc_de_Beauval\"}, {\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.740619570575527e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3079, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998051753399, \"rank\": 9.708419709935011e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French zoo sent two 17-year-old pandas - Huan Huan, a female, and her partner Yuan Zi - back to China last month after 13 years on loan in France.\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3092, \"end\": 3098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7482279226409366, \"rank\": 0.23350751323233251, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3170, \"end\": 3177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Zi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yuan Zi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Zi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Zi\"}, {\"begin\": 3188, \"end\": 3193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999995268855155, \"rank\": 4.6625125858211624e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3231, \"end\": 3237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998051753399, \"rank\": 9.708419709935011e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yuan Meng was their cub, conceived using artificial insemination.\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3240, \"end\": 3249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yuan Meng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite being made in France, he officially belonged to the Chinese government.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3329, \"end\": 3335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998051753399, \"rank\": 9.708419709935011e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3367, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999985876393991, \"rank\": 1.4123627766059717e-06, \"text\": \"Chinese government\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yuan Meng bid ''adieu'' to France in 2023, sent off to a new life in the Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding in southwest China where Brigitte Macron, considered to be his \\\"godmother,\\\" dropped in to see him.\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3387, \"end\": 3396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yuan Meng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Meng\"}, {\"begin\": 3414, \"end\": 3420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998051753399, \"rank\": 9.708419709935011e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3460, \"end\": 3467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chengdu\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.574336714108922e-13, \"text\": \"Chengdu\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chengdu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chengdu\"}, {\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giant_panda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.336626728438418e-81, \"text\": \"Giant Panda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giant_panda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giant_panda\"}, {\"begin\": 3509, \"end\": 3524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southwest_China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"southwest China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southwest_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southwest_China\"}, {\"begin\": 3531, \"end\": 3546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brigitte Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Huan Huan and Yuan Zi also produced female twins in France in 2021.\", \"from\": 3606, \"to\": 3673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Zi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yuan Zi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Zi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuan_Zi\"}, {\"begin\": 3658, \"end\": 3664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998051753399, \"rank\": 9.708419709935011e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Huanlili and Yuandudu are also expected to leave the Beauval Zoo for China in the future.\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The China Wildlife Conservation Association has previously said that it expects them to remain at the French zoo until January 2027.\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3769, \"end\": 3774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999995268855155, \"rank\": 4.6625125858211624e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3867, \"end\": 3873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7482279226409366, \"rank\": 0.23350751323233251, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in a decade, hunters armed with rifles and crossbows are fanning out across Florida's swamps and flatwoods to legally hunt the Florida black bear, over the vocal opposition of critics.\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 4102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3994, \"end\": 4001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The state-sanctioned hunt began Saturday, after drawing more than 160,000 applications for a far more limited number of hunting permits, including from opponents who are trying to reduce the number of bears killed in this year's hunt, the state's first since 2015, The Associated Press reported.\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4373, \"end\": 4389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999995452526, \"rank\": 4.5474480644892836e-10, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission awarded 172 bear hunt permits by random lottery for this year's season, allowing hunters to kill one bear each in areas where the population is deemed large enough.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4405, \"end\": 4412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least 43 of the permits went to opponents of the hunt who never intend to use them, according to the Florida chapter of the Sierra Club, which encouraged critics to apply in the hopes of saving bears.\", \"from\": 4620, \"to\": 4823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4724, \"end\": 4731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}, {\"begin\": 4747, \"end\": 4758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Club\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.60825024829776e-25, \"text\": \"Sierra Club\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Florida black bear population is considered one of the state's conservation success stories, having grown from just several hundred bears in the 1970s to an estimated more than 4,000 today.\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 5018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Opponents have questioned whether the hunt was necessary, but they were unable to convince the courts to halt it.\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what to know.\", \"from\": 5135, \"to\": 5155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A limit of one bear per hunter The 172 people who were awarded a permit through a random lottery will be able to kill one bear each during the 2025 season, which runs from Dec. 6 to Dec. 28.\", \"from\": 5157, \"to\": 5347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The permits are specific to one of the state's four designated bear hunting zones, each of which have a hunting quota set by state officials based on the bear population in each region.\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to participate, hunters must hold a valid hunting license and a bear harvest permit, which costs $100 for residents and $300 for nonresidents, plus fees.\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Applications for the permits cost $5 each.\", \"from\": 5698, \"to\": 5740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The regulated hunt will help incentivize maintaining healthy bear populations, and help fund the work that is needed, according to Mark Barton of the Florida chapter of Backcountry Hunters and Anglers, an advocacy group that supported the hunt.\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5873, \"end\": 5884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_O._Barton\", \"score\": 0.9999996500637892, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Barton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_O._Barton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_O._Barton\"}, {\"begin\": 5892, \"end\": 5899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having an annual hunt will help guarantee funding to \\\"keep moving conservation for bears forward,\\\" Barton said.\", \"from\": 5988, \"to\": 6099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6087, \"end\": 6093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demesne\", \"score\": 0.9964082497657656, \"rank\": 0.003604697406801381, \"text\": \"Barton\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demesne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demesne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hunting as a management tool According to state wildlife officials, the bear population has grown enough to support a regulated hunt and warrant population management.\", \"from\": 6101, \"to\": 6268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The state agency sees hunting as an effective tool that is used to manage wildlife populations around the world, and allows the state to monetize conservation efforts through permit and application fees.\", \"from\": 6269, \"to\": 6472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While we have enough suitable bear habitat to support our current bear population levels, if the four largest subpopulations continue to grow at current rates, we will not have enough habitat at some point in the future,\\\" reads a bear hunting guide published by the state wildlife commission.\", \"from\": 6474, \"to\": 6767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6747, \"end\": 6755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wildlife\", \"score\": 0.999999999742613, \"rank\": 2.571201635022594e-10, \"text\": \"wildlife\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wildlife\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wildlife\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opponents meanwhile have called the hunt cruel, unnecessary and an excuse for hunters to bag a trophy animal when the real issue is the ever-growing human population encroaching on bear habitat.\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stricter regulations than the last hunt This year's hunting plan has more stringent rules than the 2015 hunt, in which permits were provided to anyone who could pay for them, resulting in more than 3,700 permits issued.\", \"from\": 6965, \"to\": 7184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That led to a chaotic event that was shut down days early.\", \"from\": 7185, \"to\": 7243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of the 304 bears killed, at least 38 were females with cubs, meaning the young bears may have died too.\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, wildlife officials decided to call off the hunt after its second day after a higher than expected number of bears were killed, though hunters did not exceed the statewide quota.\", \"from\": 7349, \"to\": 7538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Doug Moore regularly sees bears on the more than 6,000 acres of timberland that he manages in northeast Florida.\", \"from\": 7540, \"to\": 7652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7545, \"end\": 7550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.5822766930591649, \"rank\": 0.7173965778136162, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 7644, \"end\": 7651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The president of a local hunting club, Moore is generally supportive of the new regulations for the bear hunt, even though he and his family members were not issued a permit this year.\", \"from\": 7653, \"to\": 7837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7692, \"end\": 7697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.5822766930591649, \"rank\": 0.7173965778136162, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moore described the management of the 2015 hunt as \\\"fouled up\\\" and \\\"totally wrong\\\" but said, \\\"they are doing it right this time.\\\"\", \"from\": 7839, \"to\": 7968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Activists were issued dozens of permits Backers of the hunt have said that growing numbers of bears present a safety problem, with local officials sharing reports of bears on porches, rooting through garbage cans and roaming neighborhoods and playgrounds.\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 8225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Activists have argued that the state should instead focus on other means of curbing nuisance bears and assuring safety through better trash management.\", \"from\": 8227, \"to\": 8378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While opponents failed to convince a judge to stop the hunt, they were issued about a quarter of the overall permits, after activists applied for hunting tags they never intend to use.\", \"from\": 8380, \"to\": 8564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Somewhere out there a bear will be walking the grounds of the Panhandle, and I gave them a stay of execution,\\\" said Joel Cleveland, an opponent of the hunt who was issued one of the permits.\", \"from\": 8566, \"to\": 8757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8688, \"end\": 8697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\", \"score\": 0.8731683470142257, \"rank\": 0.14525452442177036, \"text\": \"Cleveland\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A micro artist said he has beaten his own world record by creating the smallest handmade sculpture ever.\", \"from\": 8759, \"to\": 8863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"David A Lindon, from Bournemouth, Dorset, says his latest sculpture, The Yellow Smiley Face, is \\\"invisible to the human eye,\\\" with measurements of only 11.037 by 12.330 microns, according to BBC.\", \"from\": 8865, \"to\": 9060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8873, \"end\": 8879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}, {\"begin\": 8886, \"end\": 8897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bournemouth\", \"score\": 0.9999999996443876, \"rank\": 3.558296567529667e-10, \"text\": \"Bournemouth\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bournemouth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bournemouth\"}, {\"begin\": 8899, \"end\": 8905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorset\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.041801248277773e-15, \"text\": \"Dorset\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorset\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorset\"}, {\"begin\": 8945, \"end\": 8956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.33803129408417e-49, \"text\": \"Smiley Face\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\"}, {\"begin\": 9056, \"end\": 9059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9984114833355686, \"rank\": 0.0015910438296974658, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lindon said his artwork lived on a first-class stamp on a micro dot on the eye of the late Queen.\", \"from\": 9062, \"to\": 9159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9062, \"end\": 9068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has now broken his previous smallest handmade sculpture world record, The Lego Brick.\", \"from\": 9161, \"to\": 9249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9238, \"end\": 9242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lego\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.162565819866807e-13, \"text\": \"Lego\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lego\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lego\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lindon, who has 12 Guinness World Records in total, is known for his work creating miniature pieces of art, including three microscopic re-creations of Van Gogh masterpieces on a watch mechanism which sold for \\u00a390,000.\", \"from\": 9251, \"to\": 9469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9251, \"end\": 9257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}, {\"begin\": 9270, \"end\": 9292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.029739423524005e-53, \"text\": \"Guinness World Records\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Red Lego Brick measures 0.02517mm by 0.02184mm.\", \"from\": 9471, \"to\": 9522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My Yellow Smiley Face artwork is half the size of my Red Lego Brick artwork, which in turn was already four times smaller than the previous record,\\\" the artist said.\", \"from\": 9524, \"to\": 9690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said it was the same size as either a human blood cell, mould spores, bacteria, talcum powder and a fog droplet.\", \"from\": 9692, \"to\": 9807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other of Lindon's tiny creations include unique animals crafted within the eye of a needle, from a blue whale to a delicate peacock butterfly.\", \"from\": 9809, \"to\": 9951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9818, \"end\": 9824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I probably am completely bonkers,\\\" he jokes.\", \"from\": 9953, \"to\": 9998, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stamp where Yellow Smiley Face lives is mounted on a glass tower and housed inside a sealed glass box.\", \"from\": 10000, \"to\": 10106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10023, \"end\": 10034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.33803129408417e-49, \"text\": \"Smiley Face\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u0627\\u0646\\u0634\\u0626 \\u062d\\u0633\\u0627\\u0628\\u0627\\u064b \\u062e\\u0627\\u0635\\u0627\\u064b \\u0628\\u0643 \\u0644\\u062a\\u062d\\u0635\\u0644 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0623\\u062e\\u0628\\u0627\\u0631 \\u0645\\u062e\\u0635\\u0635\\u0629 \\u0644\\u0643 \\u0648\\u0644\\u062a\\u062a\\u0645\\u062a\\u0639 \\u0628\\u062e\\u0627\\u0635\\u064a\\u0629 \\u062d\\u0641\\u0638 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0642\\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u062a \\u0648\\u062a\\u062a\\u0644\\u0642\\u0649 \\u0646\\u0634\\u0631\\u0627\\u062a\\u0646\\u0627 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0628\\u0631\\u064a\\u062f\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062a\\u0646\\u0648\\u0639\\u0629\", \"from\": 10108, \"to\": 10214, \"entities\": []}]}"